OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1784663291
OL,3,CThames Water creditors make last-ditch
OL,4,Cbid to avoid nationalisation
OL,6,FFor the past year, it has been trying
OL,7,Fto agree a restructuring plan with the
OL,8,Fregulator, Ofwat, that would allow it
OL,9,Fto take formal control of the business.
OL,11,FUntil this morning, the consortium had
OL,12,Findicated it had made its final
OL,13,Fproposal for turning around the
OL,14,Fcompany.
OL,16,FNow, however, it is offering further
OL,17,Fconcessions, including greater control
OL,18,Ffor the government.
OL,20,FUnder the proposal, ministers would be
OL,21,Foffered a golden share in Thames Water.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1784663291
OL,3,CThames Water creditors make last-ditch
OL,4,Cbid to avoid nationalisation
OL,6,FThis would not confer ownership but
OL,7,Fwould grant veto rights over key
OL,8,Fdecisions, similar to those attached
OL,9,Fto the government's golden share in
OL,10,FRoyal Mail.
OL,12,FLondon & Valley says the details still
OL,13,Fneed to be agreed, but they could
OL,14,Finclude a veto over the sale of key
OL,15,Fassets, increases in debt and even
OL,16,Fchanges in ownership.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1784663291
OL,3,CThames Water creditors make last-ditch
OL,4,Cbid to avoid nationalisation
OL,6,FThe consortium also says it is willing
OL,7,Fto establish new "public-interest
OL,8,Fsupervisory structures," allowing
OL,9,Flocal authorities and the Mayor of
OL,10,FLondon to engage directly with the
OL,11,Fboard, providing greater scrutiny of
OL,12,FThames Water's business plans and more
OL,13,Finfluence over investment projects.
OL,15,F"Bills going up are difficult to
OL,16,Fstomach, but we think there's a
OL,17,Fdisconnect between the company and
OL,18,Fcommunities and a misunderstanding
OL,19,Fabout where the money is going," said
OL,20,Fa source close to the consortium.
OL,26,@oD@ROUpD@XO]wD@AOU{D@`O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1784663291
OL,3,CThames Water creditors make last-ditch
OL,4,Cbid to avoid nationalisation
OL,6,F"We want to rebuild confidence."
OL,8,FThe same source said the revised
OL,9,Fturnaround proposal would be submitted
OL,10,Fto Ofwat and the new Environment
OL,11,FSecretary, Angela Eagle, in the coming
OL,12,Fweeks and would include "hundreds of
OL,13,Fmillions of pounds of additional
OL,14,Finvestment," funded by the consortium.
OL,16,FOn the campaign trail in Makerfield,
OL,17,FBurnham said there was "a very strong
OL,18,Fcase for public ownership" to resolve
OL,19,FThames Water's problems.
OL,26,@nD@AOUnD@`O]tD@YOUvD@LO]yD@XOUzD@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
